    higher = [King Ask](#King Ask) with space

*** Queen Ask

The next/cheapest (non-trump) suit is the Q ask OR trump suit over 3 or 0 response (pass without 3 keycards).

- This includes bidding past the agreed suit, e.g. 4N--5-!d--5!s with !hs agreed, but promises all
  keycards and is grand slam try.
- Could be used even with the Q to find extra trumps
- Follow on asks are specific King (not King show) or 3rd round control asks where no room to ask for a specific King

*** When can sign off at 5 level

5trump = no Q
5N = Q (or known 10+ card fit), something inconvenient (i.e. higher suit King)
    6other = 3rd round control ask (if they have something inconvenient you also cannot do a request King bid!)
5x/6x = side K, have Q trumps (or known 10+ card fit)
    6other = request King, bid 7 if you have this King
6trump = Q (or known 10+ card fit), nothing extra, fast arrival

*** When forced to slam

5x/6x = side K, have Q trumps (or known 10+ card fit)
    6other = request King, bid 7 if you have this King
5N = Q (or known 10+ card fit), nothing else biddable
    6other = 3rd round control ask (if they have something inconvenient you also cannot do a request King bid!)
6trump = no Q


